                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72111/1404a</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to all
                            <gloss type="to">Seaport Consuls</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-01-11">
                        <hi rend="italic">January 11, 1915</hi>.</date>
                </dateline>
                <p rend="center">[Circular telegram]</p>
                <p>You need not report further in response to circular instructions of November
                        22<note n="6" xml:id="d1042fn6">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, p.<ref target="#pg_634">634</ref>
                    </note> and following relative to unneutral service, except in suspicious cases.
                    You will not, however, relax your vigilance to obtain and report information
                    regarding violations of American neutrality and transshipment of cargoes at sea
                    to belligerent warships.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BWJ1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
